messages.message: Yaa, I noticed the test file uses `@mock.patch()` often, but uses `cast(mock.Mock,...)` when mocking the retrieval of marketplace version metadata. Although, this retrieval is working, since there's no `Error while getting marketplace version metadata for marketplace model` error. Rather, the folders and files I added under `'data/marketplace/'` and mocked in the picture below from `_setup_fs()` seems to be the issue
Solved! It was silly case sensitivity difference between different OSes, mine isn't case sensitive so after correcting the path in my function, it worked haha
Oh man, that’s very sad. Do you happen to know which of the local env or the Jenkins env that’s case insensitive?
haha, it is a little sad, and yep my local one isn't, while Jenkins needs the capitalization to b right
Just to confirm, you’re using a macbook, not a windows machine, right?

Oh wowww. Yeah, I can confirm that `apfs` (the filesystem that macbooks use) can either be case sensitive or insensitive. And it seems to be case-insensitive on my machine too. I am shocked and appalled.
hahaha, ya figuring out I could `cd desktop` with a little d was rly jarring :smiling_face_with_tear: lol
